"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
the second note on xxiv.1 f.</A>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note41" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Demosthenes*.html#ref41
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">41</A>
In 346 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN> they obtained the so‑called Peace of Philocrates.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note42" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Demosthenes*.html#ref42
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">42</A>
At the outbreak of the Social War (357‑355 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>) Byzantium and other allies of Athens had revolted from her.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note43" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Demosthenes*.html#ref43
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">43</A>
See
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Crassus*.html#note4
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,0,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
the note on the <I>Crassus</I>, ii.8</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note44" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Demosthenes*.html#ref44
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">44</A>
In 339 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>, Philip was deputed by the Amphictyonic Council to punish the city of Amphissa, near Delphi, for sacrilege. <I>Cf.</I> Demosthenes, <I>On the Crown</I>, §§ 143 ff.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note45" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Demosthenes*.html#ref45
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">45</A>
The second so‑called Sacred War (357‑346 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>), in which Athens aided the Phocians, and Philip the Thebans.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note46" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Demosthenes*.html#ref46
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">46</A>
Deriving <SPAN LANG="el" CLASS="Greek">Αἵμων</SPAN> from <SPAN LANG="el" CLASS="Greek">αἷμα</SPAN> (<I>blood</I>).


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note47" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Demosthenes*.html#ref47
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">47</A>
<I>i.e.</I> the god of the river Thermodon, in Cappadocia, on the banks of which the Amazons were thought to dwell. <I>Cf.</I> <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Theseus*.html#27.6
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,0,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">the <I>Theseus</I>, xxvii.6</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note48" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Demosthenes*.html#ref48
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">48</A>
At Chaeroneia, 338 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note49" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Demosthenes*.html#ref49
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">49</A>
The Greek words form an iambic tetrameter catalectic.<A CLASS="correction"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(CarelessLoeb80+'cataletic</SPAN>',WIDTH,216)"
onMouseOut="nd();">º</A>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note50" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Demosthenes*.html#ref50
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">50</A>
Philip was threatening the invasion of Asia.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note51" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Demosthenes*.html#ref51
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">51</A>
Philip was assassinated by Pausanias, one of his royal bodyguard, in 336 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN> See
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Alexander*/3.html#10.6
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,0,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
the <I>Alexander</I>, x.6</A>.<A CLASS="correction"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(CarelessLoeb80+'x.4</SPAN>',WIDTH,216)"
onMouseOut="nd();">º</A>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note52" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Demosthenes*.html#ref52
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">52</A>
<I>Against Ctesiphon</I> (or <I>On the Crown</I>), § 77.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note53" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Demosthenes*.html#ref53
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">53</A>
<I>i.e.</I> <I>Silly Madman</I>. A mock heroic poem bearing this name was attributed to Homer. <I>Cf.</I> Aeschines, <I>On the Crown</I>, § 160.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note54" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Demosthenes*.html#ref54
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">54</A>
In October, 335 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note55" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Demosthenes*.html#ref55
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">55</A>
<I>Cf.</I> Aeschines, <I>On the Crown</I>, § 161.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note56" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Demosthenes*.html#ref56
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">56</A>
From 333 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN> to 330 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>, Agis III, the king of Sparta, carried on war against Macedonia in conjunction with Persia. In the latter year he was defeated and slain by Antipater, Alexander's regent in Macedonia.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note57" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Demosthenes*.html#ref57
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">57</A>
In 336 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>, Ctesiphon proposed that Demosthenes receive a golden crown for certain public services, and Aeschines indicted Ctesiphon for proposing an illegal measure. The document (Demos. <I>De Cor.</I> § 54), from which Plutarch takes


<A ID="p59x"></A>the name of Chaerondas, the archon of 338, has been shown to be spurious. The case was tried in 330 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note58" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Demosthenes*.html#ref58
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">58</A>
This made Aeschines liable to a fine of 1,000 drachmas, and made it impossible for him to bring any future action before an Athenian court.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note59" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Demosthenes*.html#ref59
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">59</A>
Alexander's treasurer. He came to Athens in 324 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note60" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Demosthenes*.html#ref60
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">60</A>
At feasts, the cup passed from guest to guest, and the one who held it had the right of uninterrupted speech or song.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note61" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Demosthenes*.html#ref61
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">61</A>
In the second of the letters which have come down to us under his name, § 17.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note62" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Demosthenes*.html#ref62
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">62</A>
At Babylon, in May, 323 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note63" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Demosthenes*.html#ref63
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">63</A>
August 6th, 322 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN> In this battle Antipater and Craterus crushed the combined armies of the Greeks and concluded the so‑called Lamian war.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note64" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Demosthenes*.html#ref64
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">64</A>
<I>i.e.</I> thy real sentiments, in obedience to Antipater.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note65" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Demosthenes*.html#ref65
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">65</A>
An allusion to the Creon in the <I>Antigone</I> of Sophocles, by whose edict the body of Polyneices was to be left unburied (vv. 26 ff., 191 ff.).


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note66" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Demosthenes*.html#ref66
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">66</A>
An annual festival in honour of Demetrius and Persephone.

	<DIV CLASS="mynote">
	<P CLASS="b0 a0">
Thayer's Note: For comprehensive details, see the article
	<A CLASS="smallcaps" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/secondary/SMIGRA*/Thesmophoria.html
	"TARGET="princeps"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,1,WIDTH,165)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
Thesmophoria
	</A>
in Smith's <I>Dictionary of Greek and Roman Antiquities</I>.
	</P></DIV>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note67" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Demosthenes*.html#ref67
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">67</A>
This statue, the work of Polyeuctus, was erected in 280‑279 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>, on motion of Demochares, a nephew of Demosthenes.


<A ID="p77x"></A>The well-known marble statue of Demosthenes in the Vatican is thought to be a copy of it. See
	<A HREF="
https://www.perseus.tufts.edu/hopper/text?doc=Perseus:text:1999.01.0160:book=1:chapter=8
	"TARGET="offsite"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,Pausanias,WIDTH,220)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
Pausanias, <SPAN CLASS="small">I</SPAN>.8.2, with Frazer's notes</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note68" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Demosthenes*.html#ref68
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">68</A>
The son of Antipater and, later, his successor.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note69" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Demosthenes*.html#ref69
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">69</A>
See
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Demosthenes*.html#1
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
the opening sentence of the <I>Life</I></A>.



	<HR CLASS="endnotes"><A ID="endnotes_T"></A>
	<H2>
Thayer's Note:
	</H2>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note:bad_English_text" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Demosthenes*.html#ref:bad_English_text
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">a</A>
The Loeb edition's English includes the word I've crossed out, which makes no sense, or at least none that I can discern, and corresponding to nothing in the facing Greek:

<DIV CLASS="Greek prose">
	<P>
ὁ Δημάδης λαβὼν πέντε τάλαντα παρὰ τῶν ἀνδρῶν ὡμολόγησε πρεσβεύσειν καὶ δεήσεσθαι τοῦ βασιλέως ὑπὲρ αὐτῶν,
</DIV>

	<P CLASS="halfstart justify">
The slip‑up caught by Susan Rhoads, whose site includes a complete transcription of
	<A HREF="
https://elfinspell.com/ClassicalTexts/Dobson-TheGreekOrators/TheGreekOrators-Title-Preface-Contents.html
	"TARGET="offsite"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,2,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
Dobson's <I>Greek Orators</I></A>.



